<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2">GM Event on the Nameless:  Mezmo Lil'thumbs in North Ro</font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=423553" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <blockquote>
<p>Last night, the gnome Mezmo Lil'thumbs appeared at the Wizard spires in the Northern Desert of Ro, asking the adventurers in the area to bring him desert tarantula chitins for his research.</p>

<p>He was offering a platinum piece for large ones, and five gold pieces for small ones.</p>

<p>Because of the recent events involving the Plague Bringer and Firiona Vie, suspicious adventurers gathered around the wizard spires and questioned him about his intentions.  He said that he was trying to "help the world" with his research, and that his machine, when finished, would be a great asset to be used for good.  Despite the mistrust, he was quite friendly and kept up a sense of humor.</p>

<p>Eventually, he had enough chitins, and teleported back to his lab to complete his research.  Shortly after this, a Mechanoid appeared near the Wizard Spires and began attacking people gathered there.  When it attacked Nikc, we jumped in to destroy it.  Bizahnt, Nikc, and I destroyed the thing, and recovered some broken parts from it, but nothing that seemed out of the ordinary.</p>

<p>A few minutes later, Mezmo reappeared at the Dervish camp, upset that his machine had been destroyed.  We told him that it had attacked us, and he claimed that it had malfunctioned.  He asked for more chitins, which he recieved, and he said that he was sure that he'd get the next one right.  He then teleported out again.</p>

<p>No more mechanoids appeared, so I can only assume that he is being more careful.  Whether this relates to any of the other happenings lately, I can't say.</p>

<p>/ooc Nikc, Bizahnt, Tsukune and myself from Serenity Within went to North Ro to check out rumors of something going on.  The zone was rather empty, and the Mechanoid happened to appear right on top of Nikc, so we had to kill it pretty quickly.  I'm not sure what would have happened if it hadn't attacked him.  It conned blue to a level 34, as did Mezmo, and dropped some gears and sprockets.  It also feigned death once during the fight.</p>

<p>Talaen Nephele<br>
Knight of the Koada'Vie<br>
Serenity Within<br>
The Nameless</p>
</blockquote>

		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
